                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Killing VS entirely solo has been one of my longest EQ goals.  I tried and failed to do it many times before and wanted to finish the goal before hitting 70 and making him too easy.  
<br />

<br />
First the details for Venril Sathir:
<br />
- procs a 1500pt lifetap DD that has a -200 MR mod on it, but cannot proc if you have a rune up.
<br />
- has max hit of ~320.
<br />
- hits ~200 average against a 65 enc with ~1100ac.  Did a few prefight runs against him with no runes to see how much damage he can do.
<br />
- supposedly has ~18k hp.
<br />
- is pacifiable
<br />

<br />
The prefight process:
<br />
- Buff up fully with anything you can get.  As I was doing it solo the only non-DS buffs I had were A rune, SoV, VoQ, Shield of Maelin, GoD, and BoA.  However, if you want to play it safer, then you should get full raid buffs.
<br />
- DS does a significant portion of the damage so load up with a shaman-made <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=14548" target="_blank" class="postlink">DS potion</a> and vendor purchased <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=14330" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ro's Breath</a>.  (I had a 21pt click from <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=68953" target="_blank" class="postlink">my veil</a>, but I think it's doable without it)
<br />
- Get a Construct of Sathir to charm and haste him.  Give him two weapons and a haste iem; I used <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=11601" target="_blank" class="postlink">RBB</a> but I bet Velium Swiftblade would better.  I tried to charm many many mobs, but CoS was the best as far as I could tell.
<br />
- Pacify VS, pull and kill all the dark blues out from his room so they won't add on the real fight.
<br />

<br />
The Fight:
<br />
- Recharm pet for max duration.
<br />
- Dispell VS a couple of times because a shaman npc might have buffed him.
<br />
- Keep refreshing A rune every couple of rounds.  Keep in mind it's a 1500pt rune and VS has an average hit of ~200.
<br />
- 450MR will resist much of the lifetap if he eats past A rune.
<br />
- If pet breaks, WoM, and recharm.
<br />
- Melee for a little extra dps.
<br />
- GM probably needs to be used if your mana pool is kinda low.
<br />

<br />
Stuff I learned for this encounter:
<br />
- VS has an innate regen of around 180hp/sec, this was probably added in response to necros soloing him awhile back.  I estimated his regen using total damage data(pet + me did ~74k damage over 5min 12sec).
<br />
- This is a long fight and you need every bit of dps you can get to avoid lots of recharming.
<br />
- Bring a rezzer bot to rez you and keep the pet preoccupied so you don't lose a few thousand pp worth in gear to random groups in the zone killing the former pet as you may die a few times.
<br />

<br />
The result:
<br />
Here's the final <a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v334/death256/vsdown.jpg" target="_blank" class="postlink">screenshot</a> linked due to size of the one and only time I ever solo'd VS.  Nothing really to see, just a dead guy in a wall.  The loot was a wizzy stick and Pally legs.  Gecho is my cleric bot, and was there to rez me when I needed to die to get pet gear from bank.  The first time I raided VS I had the biggest rush after killing him(moreso than after beating any other encounter in EQ), but after this solo win I felt barely anything.  It was disappointing since I wanted to relive it, but those days are gone. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Judge me by what I write, and not what I <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104900" target="_blank" class="postlink">wear</a>.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
