                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've never been pro-charm nerf and was severely disappointed when they removed the neg 50 mod on CoD.
<br />

<br />
Cleric was there to only do one thing, rez me incase I died.  For this particular run I only died once because I had forgotten to get my pet gear out of bank so I killed myself and grabbed pet gear then rezzed.  The death was entirely avoidable if I remembered to get pet gear first, or if I wanted to gate and run back.
<br />

<br />
If you're letting the pet tank, then you are probably going to lose as you lose pet dps from hitting in the front, fewer DS options, enchanter melee, 850pt rune vs 1500, and lifetaps will never be resisted since your pet is MR debuffed.  As I probably should have stated in the first post, I was tanking the mob with Arcane Rune maximizing dps by meleeing, using DS potions, and keeping my pet on VS' back.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Judge me by what I write, and not what I <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104900" target="_blank" class="postlink">wear</a>.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
